## Surcharge on income-tax

The amount of income-tax computed in accordance with the preceding provisions of this Paragraph, or the provisions of section 111A or section 112 or section 112A of the Incometax Act, shall be increased by a surcharge for the purposes of the Union, calculated, in the case of every individual or Hindu undivided  family  or  association  of  persons  or  body  of individuals,  whether  incorporated  or not,  or  every  artificial juridical person referred to in sub-clause (vii) of clause (31) of section 2 of the Income-tax Act,-

(a) having a total income (including the income by way of  dividend  or  income  under  the  provisions  of  section 111A,  section  112  and  section  112A  of  the  Income-tax Act)  exceeding  fifty  lakh  rupees  but  not  exceeding  one crore rupees, at the rate of ten per cent. of such incometax;

